article.description: — Gibson Jimerson scored 30 points and Saint Louis held off Rhode Island 94-91 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Jimerson scores 30 as Saint Louis holds off Rhode Island 94-91
article.linkText: Jimerson scores 30 as Saint Louis holds off Rhode Island 94-91
article.story: KINGSTON, R.I. -- — Gibson Jimerson scored 30 points and Saint Louis held off Rhode Island 94-91 on Saturday night. Jimerson added three steals for the Billikens (11-18, 4-12 Atlantic 10 Conference). Larry Hughes Jr. hit three 3-pointers and scored 17. Sincere Parker had 16 points and went 7 of 11 from the field. David Green led the way for the Rams (11-18, 5-11) with 21 points. Luis Kortright added 20 points, eight rebounds and eight assists. Jaden House had 14 points. The Rams have lost six in a row. Jimerson scored 21 points in the second half for the Billikens, who led 40-39 at intermission. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
